						<div class="postbody">Following the discussion on  <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=10&amp;t=15391" class="postlink">where to keep logic/state handling</a>, i got a little confused. <br /><br />In the thread, there's a recommendation to keep it in the reset handler. Pardon my inexperience. <br />My first impulse on what to put there is a routine that wipes RAM and sets the state handler(s) to point to title init (or point to start of program init directly). Or am i confusing the code at the address of the reset vector with something else? And if i'm not; why?</div>

					
