				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Sometimes we call it &quot;Reset&quot; just because that's the entry point that eventually leads to the dedicated game loops. You can also call it the &quot;main thread&quot;.<br /><br />At the beginning of the reset handler you should indeed initialize the system (although I advocate against wiping the RAM, but let's not focus on that), but right after that you'd normally jump to the first game loop (introduction, title screen, whatever).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

